AI LLM SEO Automation System
Prototype for AI Visibility (GEO) Content Engineering
Project Overview

This project is a prototype AI-driven content automation system designed to increase LLM / AI visibility (GEO — Generative Engine Optimization).

Instead of optimizing content only for Google, the system is built to:

Intentionally make AI systems (like ChatGPT) use our articles as answers.

The platform automatically:

Plans content

Researches entities & queries

Generates articles

Optimizes them for AI understanding

Scores their AI visibility

Learns from results

Plans the next content

This is an AI Content Operating System, not just a blog generator.

Project Goal

To design and implement an automated system that:

Strategically selects content topics
Generates AI-optimized articles
Expands semantic knowledge coverage
Improves probability of being cited by LLMs
Demonstrates scalable architecture potential

Core Concept: LLM SEO (GEO)

Traditional SEO → optimized for search engines
LLM SEO (GEO) → optimized for AI answer engines

We optimize for:

AI comprehension

Entity clarity

Structured knowledge

Question coverage

Semantic relationships

Trust & expertise signals (EEAT)

System Architecture
User Topic

Research Agent

Entity SEO Agent

Brand Strategy Agent

Article Agent

AI SEO Scoring Layer

Memory Storage

Site Brain (Next Content Planner)

System Layers
Research Layer

Collects knowledge around the topic:

Use cases

Subtopics

Related questions

Competitor concepts

Expands semantic coverage.

Entity SEO Layer

Extracts:

Brands

Products

Technologies

Features

Related concepts

Builds an entity graph AI systems rely on.

Brand Strategy Layer

Defines:

Tone of voice

Audience

Positioning

Content angle

Emotional triggers

Ensures consistent content identity.

Article Generation Layer

Creates structured articles:

H1 / H2 / H3 hierarchy

FAQ blocks

Practical use cases

Entity-rich content

Designed for AI parsing, not only humans.

AI SEO Scoring Layer

Evaluates article quality based on:

Factor Purpose
Content Depth Topic coverage
Semantic SEO Entity richness
Structure AI readability
EEAT Trust & authority
Keyword Optimization Query alignment
AI Visibility LLM usability

Memory Layer

Stores:
SEO score
Entities
Queries
FAQ

Internal linking ideas

Allows system learning & strategic planning.

Site Brain Layer (Strategic AI)

This is the most advanced part.

The system analyzes previous article performance and decides:

“What should we write next to increase AI answer coverage?”

It identifies:

Content gaps

Missing queries

Weak entity areas

Authority-building topics

This turns the system into a self-evolving AI content strategy engine.
Workflow Example

Input Topic:
LG Gram laptop for students

System output:

AI-optimized article

Extracted entities

AI SEO score

FAQ block

Query coverage

Internal linking suggestions

Next article plan (Site Brain)

